# <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# Example:
# feat(auth): add JWT token expiration check

# Commit types:
# - feat     : A new feature
# - fix      : A bug fix
# - chore    : Maintenance (build, deps, infra)
# - docs     : Documentation only
# - style    : Formatting, no logic change
# - refactor : Refactoring code
# - test     : Adding or updating tests
# - perf     : Performance improvements
# - ci       : CI/CD config

# Optional scopes (use your domain: auth, api, db, ui, kafka, etc.)
# Keep the summary under 72 characters.

# --- BODY (optional, remove this line if unused) ---
#
# Add detailed explanation of the commit.
# Describe the motivation and the context.
# Use bullet points if needed:
#
# - What changed and why
# - Side effects or risks
# - How to test it
#

# --- FOOTERS (optional, remove any line not needed) ---
#
# Closes: #123              # Closes the related issue
# Fixes: #456               # Fixes a specific bug
# Co-authored-by: Full Name <email@example.com>  # Multiple authors
# Reviewed-by: Full Name <email@example.com>     # Code review credit
# BREAKING CHANGE: description of breaking change
